<task id="068" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>FileSummarizationService — gpt-4o-mini 1-paragraph precomputed summary (NEW)</title>
    <phase>4: WP5 6-Tier Memory Subsystem (sub-WP 4b)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>064</dependencies>
    <blocks>070,073,076</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, services, ai, azure-openai, ADR-013, ADR-015</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New BFF service with LLM call; ADR-013 + ADR-015 binding; output marked NOT authoritative per P3 trust framing</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>NEW file — no overlap with peer 4-B tasks</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author `FileSummarizationService` (NEW). Uses `gpt-4o-mini` to produce a 1-paragraph precomputed summary of an uploaded file per architecture §4.4 + §6.1. Output is explicitly marked as "NOT authoritative" per architecture P3 (P3: citation-bearing trust model — precomputed summaries are upload-time approximations). The summary feeds the layered context card (task 076) but the persona instruction (task 077) tells the LLM not to quote it as the source.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in Azure OpenAI summarization + trust-framing semantics per architecture P3.</role>

  <goal>
    `FileSummarizationService.cs` exists with `IFileSummarizationService` interface + `SummarizeAsync(string textContent, string fileName, string contentType, CancellationToken ct) → FileSummarizationResult`. Returns 1-paragraph summary ≤120 chars (architecture §6.1 target). Implementation calls gpt-4o-mini with a system prompt that produces concise factual summary. ADR-015 tier-1 logging — NEVER log textContent OR the summary text body.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer.</role>

  <goal>
    `FileSummarizationService.cs` shipped with `IFileSummarizationService` + `SummarizeAsync` returning a 1-paragraph (≤120 chars) precomputed summary marked as upload-time approximation. The summary becomes part of the layered context card (076) but the trust-framing instruction (077) ensures the agent calls `recall_session_file` for any legally-precise answer.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §4.4 + §6.1 + P3. Companion service to 067 (classification) and 069 (manifest). Output stored in `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[].SummaryText` after task 071 extension; persisted by task 072. The 120-char target keeps the static prefix budget under 6K tokens (architecture §10.2). Summary is INPUT to layered context card builder (076) — it is NOT meant to be cited; the trust frame (077) reinforces this.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IOpenAiClient.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service lives in `Services/Ai/` — direct `IOpenAiClient` consumption OK.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging: fileId, sessionId, durationMs, summary CHAR LENGTH only. NEVER the summary text or input textContent.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture P3">Output is "NOT authoritative" — the architectural responsibility of the summarization service is to PRODUCE the summary; the trust-framing responsibility (telling the LLM not to quote it) lives in task 077.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §6.1">Uses `gpt-4o-mini`; target ~250ms parallel; output ≤120 chars.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No new external API (no Document Intelligence). Use Azure OpenAI only.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
